    "Therefore, the 6DOF case study corroborates the findings from the CD case study, reinforcing the importance of diversity in the fitness function for effective WCET estimation in complex, real-time systems.Figures 5.4b and 5.4a from the 6-DOF case study show the GA's performance in terms of maximum execution time fitness scores.",
    "When only execution time is considered, the GA exhibits limited variability, indicating constrained exploration and potential premature convergence.",
    "In contrast, incorporating diversity into the fitness evaluation results in a more consistent increase in execution times, promoting broader exploration and enhancing the reliability of the WCET estimation process.",
    "RQ1 ConclusionFor both case studies, the GA with diversity as a fitness function outperformed the one without diversity as a fitness function.",
    "RQ2In addressing Research Question 2, our investigation centers on evaluating the performance of the RL approach under different scenarios."
